  "texts": [
    "Gao et al. (2022) compared TASO-BERT-CRF, PARAPHRASE (Zhang et al. 2021d), and GAS (Zhang et al. 2021a), with his proposed LEGO-ABSA (multi-task) and LEGO-ABSA (separate) and demonstrate that the LEGO-ABSA models outperform them, as shown in Table 9.",
    "LEGO-ABSA conducts experiments on multiple benchmark datasets, demonstrating that its multi-task framework achieves new state-of-the-art results in almost all tasks and competitive results in task transfer scenarios.",
    "The approach has also shown competitive results in cross-domain scenarios, demonstrating its effectiveness in handling ABSA tasks in different domains.",
    "However, there is still room for improvement in the approach's performance in cross-domain scenarios, and further research is needed to address this challenge.",
    "Varia et al. (2022) proposed a unified instruction Tuning framework for few-shot ABSA tasks."
